  "text": "## End-to-End Kubernetes Deployment Creation\n\n### Layer 1: Client Library (kubernetes-client-go)\n\nWhen a user creates a Deployment using the Kubernetes Go client, the flow begins in **client-go--v0.32.0/gentype/type.go** at the `Client[T].Create()` method (line 244). This generic method constructs an HTTP POST request using the REST client:\n\n```go\nerr := c.client.Post().\n    UseProtobufAsDefaultIfPreferred(c.prefersProtobuf).\n    NamespaceIfScoped(c.namespace, c.namespace != \"\").\n    Resource(c.resource).\n    VersionedParams(&opts, c.parameterCodec).\n    Body(obj).\n    Do(ctx).\n    Into(result)\n```\n\nThe REST client implementation is in **client-go--v0.32.0/rest/request.go**, which handles the low-level HTTP communication with the API server.\n\n### Layer 2: API Server (kubernetes/kubernetes)\n\nOn the server side, the HTTP POST request is handled by the `createHandler` function in **kubernetes--v1.32.0/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/handlers/create.go** (line 53). This handler:\n\n1. Parses the request body and validates the Deployment object\n2. Runs admission controllers\n3. Calls `r.Create()` where `r` is the `REST` struct from **kubernetes--v1.32.0/pkg/registry/apps/deployment/storage/storage.go** (line 88)\n\nThe `REST` struct inherits from `genericregistry.Store` and delegates the actual creation to `Store.Create()` in **kubernetes--v1.32.0/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/registry/generic/registry/store.go** (line 446). This method:\n\n1. Validates the Deployment object\n2. Calls the CreateStrategy\n3. Most importantly, calls `e.Storage.Create()` at line 526, where `Storage` is the etcd backend interface\n\n### Layer 3: Storage & etcd Backend\n\nThe storage layer is implemented in **kubernetes--v1.32.0/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/store.go** with the `store.Create()` method (line 241). This method:\n\n1. Encodes the Deployment object using the registered codec\n2. Encrypts the data if configured\n3. Calls `s.client.Kubernetes.OptimisticPut()` at line 283\n\nThe `s.client` is an etcd v3 client from **etcd-io-etcd/client/v3/kubernetes/client.go** at `Client.OptimisticPut()` (line 83). This creates an optimistic transaction:\n\n```go\ntxn := k.KV.Txn(ctx).If(\n    clientv3.Compare(clientv3.ModRevision(key), \"=\", expectedRevision),\n).Then(\n    clientv3.OpPut(key, string(value), clientv3.WithLease(opts.LeaseID)),\n)\ntxnResp, err := txn.Commit()\n```\n\nThe transaction is committed via **etcd-io-etcd/client/v3/txn.go** at `txn.Commit()` (line 137), which sends a gRPC call to the etcd server's KV service.\n\n### etcd Server: Transaction Execution\n\nThe etcd server receives the transaction at **etcd-io-etcd/server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/key.go** in `kvServer.Txn()` (line 83). This RPC handler validates the request and calls `s.kv.Txn()` at line 95, where `s.kv` is the `RaftKV` interface.\n\nThe actual transaction is applied in **etcd-io-etcd/server/etcdserver/apply.go** via `applierV3backend.Txn()` (line 430), which:\n\n1. Evaluates the transaction's comparison conditions\n2. Executes the appropriate branch (success or failure)\n3. For Put operations, calls `applierV3backend.Put()` (line 249)\n\nThe `Put()` method:\n\n1. Handles lease assignment and previous value retrieval\n2. Calls `txn.Put(p.Key, val, leaseID)` at line 300\n\n### Final Persistence: MVCC Storage\n\nThe actual persistence happens in **etcd-io-etcd/server/mvcc/kvstore_txn.go** with `storeTxnWrite.Put()` (line 109), which delegates to `storeTxnWrite.put()` (line 190). This method:\n\n1. Marshals the KeyValue protobuf\n2. Calls `tw.tx.UnsafeSeqPut(buckets.Key, ibytes, d)` at line 226\n3. Updates the in-memory index tree\n4. Manages lease associations\n\nThe `tw.tx` is a transaction on the underlying bolt database (bbolt), which provides the atomic, persistent key-value store backend for etcd."
}

